# Next.js 15 Optimization

## Configuration
- Use Turbopack for faster development builds
- Configure SVG support in [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts)
- Enable `dangerouslyAllowSVG` for team logos
- Set proper content security policies

## Image Optimization
- Use `next/image` for all images, including SVGs
- Specify width and height for proper sizing
- Use `alt` attributes for accessibility
- Configure image domains if needed

## Performance Best Practices
- Use dynamic imports for heavy components
- Implement proper loading states
- Minimize bundle size by removing unused code
- Use `use client` directive only when necessary

## Build Optimization
- Fix all TypeScript errors before deployment
- Remove unused imports and variables
- Use proper dependency arrays in useEffect
- Avoid React Hook warnings

## SEO and Meta
- Update page titles and meta descriptions
- Use proper semantic HTML structure
- Include favicon and app icons
- Configure robots.txt if needed

## Error Handling
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Handle loading and error states
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Use Next.js error pages when appropriate

## Development Workflow
- Use `npm run dev` for development
- Use `npm run build` to check for errors
- Fix linting warnings before deployment
- Test responsive behavior on different devices

## File Organization
- Keep components in `src/components/`
- Use proper imports with `@/` alias
- Organize assets in `public/` directory
- Follow consistent naming conventions